{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer overflow in UL channel bandwidth calculation\n\n### Summary\nThe `compare_relative_ul_channel_bw` function in the NR common utilities was vulnerable to integer overflow when calculating the relative UL channel bandwidth for certain frequency bands. This occurred during the computation `(2 * band_size_khz) / (nr_bandtable[index].ul_max + nr_bandtable[index].ul_min)` where intermediate arithmetic could exceed the range of the `int` type.\n\nThe issue primarily affected FR2 bands with high frequency values (e.g., band 257 with frequencies around 26-29 GHz) when combined with large bandwidth configurations. The overflow could cause incorrect power control decisions in the UE MAC layer.\n\nThis fix addresses the vulnerability by:\n1. Performing arithmetic using `double` precision to prevent overflow\n2. Explicitly casting operands to ensure proper type promotion\n3. Maintaining the same mathematical relationship while improving numerical stability\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/nr/nr_common.c`: Updated `compare_relative_ul_channel_bw` to use double precision arithmetic and explicit casting for overflow protection.\n\n"
}